{"tid":2418654,"cid":5,"subCid":11,"title":"歐盟面對香港最新局勢，宣布有以下措施應對：","createTime":"2021-02-22T19:52:45.000Z","updateTime":"2021-02-27T20:05:50.000Z","uid":28114,"like":259,"dislike":12,"uniUserReply":66,"replies":[{"pid":"00b1e748b8f08270485a45d4b358e6e9e5f37e00","tid":2418654,"uid":28114,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2021-02-22T19:52:45.000Z","msg":"Europe to Tip Toward U.S.&rsquo;s Tougher Stance on Russia, China<br />\nEU foreign ministers will order sanctions over Russia&rsquo;s jailing of Alexei Navalny<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.wsj.com/articles/europe-set-to-tip-toward-u-s-s-tougher-stance-on-russia-china-11613994944\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Feurope-set-to-tip-toward-u-s-s-tougher-stance-on-russia-china-11613994944&d=x6KcuROq%2Bx9sojjRb0T2Xi%2F0jIrp0bHqVoz25JuQVd4%3D&h=275129c6\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.wsj.com/articles/europe-set-to-tip-toward-u-s-s-tougher-stance-on-russia-china-11613994944</a><br />\n<br />\n歐盟外長們也同意採取一些措施，以回應中國對香港日益崩緊的控制。<br />\n<br />\n鮑雷爾週一晚間說，部長們已同意擴大與香港民間社會團體的聯繫，與香港志同道合的國際夥伴進行協調，並向中國當局施加壓力。<br />\n<br />\n 上週，歐盟外交部門散發了一份機密文件，概述了歐盟未來幾個月可能採取的一系列步驟。<br />\n<br />\n 該文件提出了迅速採取行動以加強與香港民主運動人士的聯繫，包括邀請主要人物參加布魯塞爾的會談。 它說，可以建立與香港公民社會團體的磋商平台，以&ldquo;根據歐盟在當地的重大經濟和金融利益，協調歐洲對香港局勢的回應。&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\n 該文件稱，歐盟應與其他民主力量&ldquo;協調對北京和香港的聯合推廣&rdquo;，包括通過七國集團。 它還提議在新成立的歐盟-美國就香港進行討論。 關於中國的雙邊對話。<br />\n<br />\n未來幾個月內將要考慮的其他措施可能是減輕跨國公司轉移香港公民到歐洲的能力，並商定在整個歐盟範圍內中止引渡條約。<br />\n<br />\n 歐盟會考慮派其人權特別代表來香港。<br />\n<br />\n 去年7月，《國家安全法》通過後，歐盟在香港採取了一些溫和的措施，該法擴大了當局逮捕分裂或顛覆活動或與外國勢力勾結的香港公民的權力。<br />\n<br />\n文件稱：&ldquo;雖然七月份通過的一攬子計劃在當時受到了好評，但隨著局勢的惡化，歐盟的立場正受到越來越多的審查。&rdquo;  &ldquo;在評估潛在措施時，也應牢記其影響中國行為的能力及其對整個中歐關係的潛在影響。&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\n歐盟與香港有著實質性的業務聯繫，超過60％的流入和流出中國的外國直接投資通過香港，並在香港設立了1500多家歐盟公司。 去年，歐盟與香港的雙邊貿易額超過270億歐元，折合330億美元。<br />\n<br />\n儘管與美國不同，歐盟已經避免對香港或中國官員進行直接制裁，但歐盟官員表示歐盟有可能實施新的人權制度。 該文件是歐盟自12月與北京簽署投資協議談判以擴大經濟聯繫以來，歐盟不會放棄對香港局勢關注的信號。"},{"pid":"21ece1bac78a31c05196d476a3edac17c8c7c3f4","tid":2418654,"uid":28114,"like":13,"dislike":0,"score":13,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-02-22T19:54:24.000Z","msg":"Hong Kong<br />\n<br />\nThe Council was informed about the deteriorating situation and agreed on a set of short and longer-term actions, in addition to the initial response package adopted last July.<br />\n<br />\nImmediate measures include increased support to civil society, stepping up coordination with like-minded partners, and outreach to relevant authorities.<br />\n<br />\nThe Council also addressed the impact of the deteriorating situation in Hong Kong on the broader relations with China.<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.consilium.europa.eu/en/meetings/fac/2021/02/22/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.consilium.europa.eu%2Fen%2Fmeetings%2Ffac%2F2021%2F02%2F22%2F&d=x6KcuROq%2Bx9sojjRb0T2Xi%2F0jIrp0bHqVoz25JuQVd4%3D&h=2905ae07\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.consilium.europa.eu/en/meetings/fac/2021/02/22/</a>"},{"pid":"3b317adfd9a976842fd9eb15ad0b3d4adc919477","tid":2418654,"uid":28114,"like":4,"dislike":0,"score":4,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-02-22T19:55:16.000Z","msg":"Last July&rsquo;s response <br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://eeas.europa.eu/headquarters/headquarters-homepage_en/82792/Foreign%20Affairs%20Council:%20Remarks%20by%20the%20High%20Representative/Vice-President%20Josep%20Borrell%20at%20the%20press%20conference\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Feeas.europa.eu%2Fheadquarters%2Fheadquarters-homepage_en%2F82792%2FForeign%2520Affairs%2520Council%3A%2520Remarks%2520by%2520the%2520High%2520Representative%2FVice-President%2520Josep%2520Borrell%2520at%2520the%2520press%2520conference&d=x6KcuROq%2Bx9sojjRb0T2Xi%2F0jIrp0bHqVoz25JuQVd4%3D&h=7a77fdfb\" target=\"_blank\">https://eeas.europa.eu/headquarters/headquarters-homepage_en/82792/Foreign%20Affairs%20Council:%20Remarks%20by%20the%20High%20Representative/Vice-President%20Josep%20Borrell%20at%20the%20press%20conference</a><br />\n<br />\nQ. The Minister of Foreign Affairs of Germany Heiko Maas over the weekend said there would be initial proposals to be tabled for discussion. Could you give us more details on what was actually discussed, does that include potential arms embargo to the Hong Kong police or does that include suspending extradition treaties with the Hong Kong authorities? What do you think can be done on the EU level as well?<br />\n<br />\nWe have agreed today to develop a coordinated European Union response to show support for Hong Kong&rsquo;s autonomy and civil society. This will comprise both measures at European Union level and also measures falling under the Member States national competence in a coordinated approach. Everything will be done in coordination with Member States and the package of measures will constitute a comprehensive European Union response. Some Member States may already announce national measures as part of this package in the coming days according with our discussions today.<br />\n<br />\nIn these discussions some ideas where under consideration. I am not going to list all of them but for example we looked at the possibility to further scrutinise the export of specific and sensitive technologies to Hong Kong. We assessed the implications of the national security law for Member States&rsquo; extradition agreement with Hong Kong and travel advice, and looked at possibilities to step-up scholarships for Hong Kong students. And we have also been discussing at European Union level the asylum and migration implications of the national security law, including looking at visa possibilities for Hongkongers, although visa are a competence of the Member States but it has been widely discussed today."},{"pid":"0dccacf01725aab5b796901c3c8367a5177c929a","tid":2418654,"uid":28114,"like":169,"dislike":10,"score":159,"citedBy":10,"replyTime":"2021-02-22T19:58:10.000Z","msg":"認真，佢搞上述嗰啲都係鳩噏，冇鳩用<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmo